## Project Implementation

This session built a GL-to-BISTA mapping tool in `/home/perni/clexp/experiments/bista-mapper/`:

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `bista_mapper.py` | Main script — reads GL CSV, applies mapping, writes BISTA CSV |
| `mapping.csv` | Account ranges → BISTA items (German GAAP / HGB / RechKredV / SKR 51) |
| `mapping_ifrs.csv` | Account ranges → BISTA items (IFRS 9 / IAS 37) |
| `sample_gl.csv` | Sample general ledger input |

### Usage

```bash
python bista_mapper.py --standard hgb              # German GAAP (default)
python bista_mapper.py --standard ifrs             # IFRS
python bista_mapper.py --mapping my_mapping.csv    # Custom mapping
```

### GL input format

```csv
account_number,description,amount_eur
0110,Kassenbestand EUR,450000.00
```

### BISTA output format

```csv
form,bista_item,bista_description,side,amount_eur
HV11,HV11_011,Barreserve - Kassenbestand,asset,450000.00
```

